  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN190.1-kilavi">tōḻi cevilittāyk kaṟattoṭu niṉṟatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">How the confidante stood firm in [her] duty to the foster mother.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="AN190.1">
        <l>tiraiyu<supplied>ḻa</supplied>n tacaii niraivaḷai yāya</l>
        <l>muppiṉ kuppai yēṟi yeṟpaṭa</l>
        <l>varutimi leṇṇun tuṟaivaṉō ṭūrē</l>
        <l>yorutaṉ koṭumaiyi ṉalarpā ṭummē</l>
        <l>yalamaraṉ maḻaikka ṇamarntu nōkkā</l>
        <l>ḷalaiyal vāḻivēṇ ṭaṉṉai yuyarmicaip</l>
        <l>potumpiṟ puṉṉaic ciṉaicēr pirunta</l>
        <l>vampa nārai yiriya vorunāṭ</l>
        <l>poṅkuvara lūtaiyoṭu puṇari yalaippavu</l>
        <l>muḻaikkaṭal vaḻaṅkalu veyya ṉakaṉṟalai</l>
        <l>yiruṅka<supplied>ḻi</supplied>p pukā<supplied>a</supplied>r poru<supplied>n</supplied>tat tākki</l>
        <l>vaiccuṟā veṟinteṉa valava ṉaḻippa</l>
        <l>veḻilpayaṅ kuṉṟiya ciṟaiyaḻi toḻi<supplied>la</supplied></l>
        <l>nirainaṭaip puravi virainaṭai tavira</l>
        <l>viḻumeṉ kāṉal viḻumaṇa lacaii</l>
        <l>yāynta pariyaṉ vantivaṇ</l>
        <l>māṉṟa mālaic cērntaṉṟō vilaṉē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>Because of the man from the ghat, (3c)</l>
        <l>where, as night falls, the girl companions with bangles in rows,</l> 
        <l>after having borne the waves [and] resting, mount the heaps of salt (1f.)</l>
        <l rend="indent4">[and] count the boats that come, (3ab)</l>
        <l>the village, it sings with gossip, in its singular cruelty. (3df.)</l>
        <l>Don’t slap her who did not look [at him], [her] fluttering rain eyes</l>
        <l>remaining steady, – oh mother, please. (5-6c)</l>
        <l>He who was keen on also roaming the nearby sea, (10a-c)</l>
        <l>although the waves were rolling, with the cold wind coming with foam, (9)</l>
        <l>on one day, so that the new egrets retreated (8)</l>
        <l>that were perched close on the branches of the Puṉṉai trees in the grove</l>
        <l rend="indent7">of tall treetops, (6df.)</l>
        <l>as for [his] having come here, he with choice horses,</l>
        <l>joining [us] on gloomy evenings, he has not, (16f.)</l>
        <l>resting in the excellent sand of the rustling seashore grove, (15)</l>
        <l>while the horses that move in rows were restrained in [their] fast gait, (14)</l>
        <l>straining against the confinement that diminished the amount of [their] grace, (13)</l>
        <l>so that the charioteer stops [them], because sharp sharks were dashing [at them], (12)</l>
        <l>attacking, as is fitting [for them], those who do not enter the dark backwaters of vast area. (10df.)</l>
        <lg type="alternate" sameAs="4b">
            <l>it sings with gossip of his singular cruelty.</l></lg>
      </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>
